    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft - Removal
        - Preliminary Checks
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26508.1.2" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="9">
        <title>Preliminary Checks</title>
        <para>Measure the following:</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Crankshaft gear to camshaft gear</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Primary balancer gear to crankshaft gear</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Crankshaft end play</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Camshaft end play</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Primary balancer shaft end play</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <figure id="f3000903" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj03/J03005.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Primary balancer gear-to-crankshaft gear backlash</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check and record primary balancer gear-to-crankshaft gear backlash as follows:</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Crankshaft gear must be fixed, not allowed to rotate. Only the primary balance gear should be
                        allowed to rotate, otherwise the reading will not be valid.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_351.xml" xrefid="E30009C">dial indicator with magnetic base</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="E30009C"/>
                    onto rear of engine.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position dial indicator tip onto a primary balancer gear tooth and remove lash.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Zero dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Rotate gear by hand and read indicator. Record backlash.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If backlash exceeds
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_349.xml" xrefid="E30009A">Specifications
                        <xref refid="E30009A"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    , replace primary balance gear.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000904" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj03/J03006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Camshaft-to-crankshaft gear backlash</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check and record camshaft gear-to-crankshaft gear backlash as follows:</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Crankshaft gear must be fixed, not allowed to rotate. Only the camshaft gear should be allowed
                        to rotate, otherwise the reading will not be valid.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_351.xml" xrefid="E30009C">dial indicator with magnetic base</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="E30009C"/>
                    onto rear of engine.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position dial indicator tip onto a cam gear tooth and remove lash.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Zero dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Rotate gear by hand and read indicator. Record backlash.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If backlash exceeds
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_349.xml" xrefid="E30009A">Specifications
                        <xref refid="E30009A"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    , replace camshaft gear.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000905" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj03/J03007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Primary balance shaft end play</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check and record primary balance shaft end play as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Reposition dial indicator tip to balance shaft, not gear.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Push camshaft towards the front of the engine.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Zero dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place a small pry bar between the primary balance gear and crankcase. Lightly pry
                    primary balance gear toward indicator. Compare dial indicator reading with
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_349.xml" xrefid="E30009A">Specifications
                        <xref refid="E30009A"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000906" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj03/J03001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Balance shaft counterweight bolt</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the balance shaft counterweight bolt (M10 x 25).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000907" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ03/J03002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Balance shaft thrust plate bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove three balance shaft thrust plate bolts (M6 x 12).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000908" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ03/J03003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Balance shaft counterweight and thrust plate</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove balance shaft counterweight and thrust plate.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000909" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ03/J03009.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Balance shaft removal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully remove balance shaft from the inside of the camshaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000910" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ03/J03008.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Camshaft end play</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Check camshaft end play only after the balance shaft has been removed.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check and record camshaft end play as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Reposition dial indicator tip onto camshaft, not gear.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Push camshaft towards the front of the engine.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Zero dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place a small pry bar or screwdriver between the camshaft gear and crankcase. Lightly
                    pry camshaft gear towards indicator. Compare dial indicator measurement with
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_349.xml" xrefid="E30009A">Specifications
                        <xref refid="E30009A"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000911" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ03/J03010.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankshaft end play</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dial indicator</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pry bar or screwdriver</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check crankshaft end play as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount dial indicator on crankcase with indicator tip on the end of crankshaft flange as
                    shown.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Pry crankshaft forward with pry bar and zero dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Pry crankshaft back and forth while reading dial indicator. Record end play
                    measurement.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
